<p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400 mb-6">Published June 15, 2026 · 5 min read</p>

<p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300 mb-8">The OUT- prefix means "surpassing" or "beyond" and is one of Scrabble's most versatile word-starters. With 400+ valid words, OUT- attaches to nearly any verb to create a competitive comparison — OUTRUN, OUTPLAY, OUTSCORE. This makes it a powerful bingo prefix and extension tool.</p>

<p>OUT- uses common 1-point tiles, making it easy to accumulate. The real value comes from combining it with high-value roots containing J, K, X, or Z.</p>

<h2 class="text-xl font-light text-amber-600 dark:text-amber-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-amber-400 pl-4">Why OUT- Matters in Scrabble</h2>

